word_mean_info__list.difference: 指朦胧出现，好像从雾中浮现出来一样。

bilingual.source: The sun began to emerge from behind the clouds.
bilingual.target: 太阳开始从云层后面出现。

bilingual.source: Cicadas emerge from the ground every few years.
bilingual.target: 蝉每隔几年就会从地下出现。

bilingual.source: As the project evolves, new challenges emerge.
bilingual.target: 随着项目逐渐发展，新的挑战出现了。

bilingual.source: As the facts emerge, the truth becomes clearer.
bilingual.target: 随着事实的出现，真相变得更加清晰。

bilingual.source: New contenders emerge every year in the tech industry.
bilingual.target: 每年在科技行业都会出现新的竞争者。

bilingual.source: After hours of discussion, a consensus began to emerge.
bilingual.target: 经过几个小时的讨论，共识开始出现。

bilingual.source: New technologies emerge every year, changing the way we live.
bilingual.target: 新技术每年都会出现，改变我们的生活方式。

bilingual.source: The butterfly will emerge from its cocoon in a few days.
bilingual.target: 蝴蝶将在几天内从茧中出现。

bilingual.source: At the confluence of art and technology, new forms of expression emerge.
bilingual.target: 在艺术和技术的汇合处，新的表达形式出现了。

bilingual.source: Interest in the old technology continues to ebb as new innovations emerge.
bilingual.target: 随着新技术的出现，人们对旧技术的兴趣持续衰退。

list.abstract: emerge（英[iˈmɜːdʒ]，美[iˈmɜːrdʒ]），英语单词，动词，指浮现、出现、出来。英语短语有：finally emerge，译为终于出现，例句为“The economy has started to emerge from recession.”（经济已开始从衰退中复苏。）

yingyinNormal.en: And someday he'll spin a cocoon and emerge two months later with moth wings and an exoskeleton.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有一天他会结一个茧，两个月后带着翅膀和外骨骼破茧而出。

yingyinNormal.en: Still, I'm sure whatever rock they decide to hide under, we'll find them as soon as they emerge.
yingyinNormal.zh: 反正，不管他们躲在哪块石头下，只要一冒头，我们就会发现他们。

yingyinNormal.en: There's J-pop, there's K-pop, there's C-pop, and there's like this W-pop, that's kind of starting to emerge. It's world pop.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有日流，有韩流，就有华流，还有一个世界流，它们开始融合。

yingyinNormal.en: Penny's brain teaser this morning. She and Koothrappali emerge from your bedroom. She is disheveled, and Raj is dressed only in a sheet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩妮今早留下的头脑风暴悬念，她跟库萨帕里从你的卧室走出，她衣衫不整，拉杰只裹了个床单。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, dear Lord. A man pops out for a moment to evacuate his bowels and catch up on the adventures of the Caped Crusader, only to emerge and discover his apartment has been transformed into a cabaret.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，真要命，人家只是走开了一下，清了清肠子，顺便追一下斗篷战士[蝙蝠侠别称]的冒险之旅，再出来就发现家里赫然变成卡巴莱酒馆了。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: n. 紧急情况；不测事件；预备队员；替补队员；第二次世界大战；急诊病人；急症病人；紧急情况下出现（或所需、使用）的；急诊室

word_family.mean: v. 浮现；出现；出来；幸存下来；变得显眼；被知晓；暴露；恢复过来；破壳而出

sense_info_list.en: move out of or away from something and come into view, as from concealment
sense_info_list.zh: 出现; 浮现; 出来

examination_example.sentence: Pairs of opponents hit the ball back and forth until one winner <highlight>emerges</highlight> from all who entered.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 成对的对手来回击球，直到所有参赛者中出现一名获胜者。

examination_example.sentence: An 84-year-old widow recently <highlight>emerged</highlight> from her small, tin-roofed house in Florida.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一位84岁的遗孀最近从她位于佛罗里达州的锡屋顶小房子里走出来。

examination_example.sentence: An <highlight>emerging</highlight> body of research shows that positive health habits spread through networks of friends via social communication.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一项新兴研究表明，良好的健康习惯通过社交在朋友圈中传播。

sense_info_list.en: happen or occur as a result of something; become apparent, important, or prominent

examination_example.sentence: Guilt <highlight>emerges</highlight> a little later, in conjunction with a child's growing grasp of social and moral norms.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着孩子对社会和道德规范的日益，内疚感会凸显得晚一些。

examination_example.sentence: The United States <highlight>emerged</highlight> as an international power.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国崛起，成为世界强国。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Emerging</highlight> in the late Sixties and reaching a peak in the Seventies, Land Art was one of a range of new forms.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大地艺术出现于六十年代后期，并在七十年代达到鼎盛时期，是一系列新形式中的其中一种。

sense_info_list.en: recover from or survive a difficult or demanding situation
sense_info_list.zh: 恢复过来; 幸存下来

examination_example.sentence: You and your children will benefit and <highlight>emerge</highlight> from stressful moments feeling better physically and emotionally.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你和你的孩子将受益，并从紧张的时刻中走出来，身体和情绪都感觉更好。

sense_info_list.en: become known, especially as a result of examining something or asking questions about it

word_usage.usage:
表达“出现”
emerge指从某个掩蔽处出现或摆脱遮挡物而被看见，强调缓缓出现的过程，常后接介词 from。
appear强调进入视野为人所见，也指公开露面为公众所看见。loom尤指轮廓不清、令人惊恐地隐现。
arise多指问题、困境等出现。

sense_info_list.en: move out of or away from something and come into view, as from concealment

examination_example.sentence: When it <highlight>emerged</highlight> towards the end of the 1980s as a purely text-based medium, it was seen as a tool to pursue knowledge.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当它在20世纪80年代末作为一种纯文本媒体出现时，它被视为追求知识的工具。

examination_example.sentence: There is also a growing body of evidence that diet-induced cognitive impairments can <highlight>emerge</highlight> rapidly—within weeks or even days.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 越来越多的证据表明，饮食导致的认知障碍会在几周甚至几天内迅速出现。

examination_example.sentence: The revelation of how close France came to losing its most famous cathedral <highlight>emerged</highlight>.

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全四级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

word_family.mean: v. 浮现；出现；出来；幸存下来；变得显眼；被知晓；暴露；恢复过来；破壳而出

sense_info_list.en: happen or occur as a result of something; become apparent; important; or prominent

examination_example.sentence: Furthermore, most adult cases of clinical depression first <highlight>emerge</highlight> in adolescence (青春期) .
examination_example.sentence_trans: 此外，大多数成人临床抑郁症病例首先出现在青春期。

examination_example.sentence: But lower cost options are <highlight>emerging</highlight>, too.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但成本更低的选择也在不断涌现。

examination_example.sentence: It's also a trend that <highlight>emerged</highlight> decades ago and has simply stuck.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这也是几十年前出现的一种趋势，只是一直没有改变。

sense_info_list.en: move out of or away from something and come into view; as from concealment

examination_example.sentence: Those are a few of the traits of successful science crowd funding efforts that <highlight>emerge</highlight> from a recent study that examined nearly 400 campaigns, But having a large network and some promotional skis may be more crucial.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最近的一项研究对近400项活动进行了调查，结果显示这些是成功的科学众筹活动的一些特征。但是拥有一个庞大的数据网络和一些推广技巧可能更为重要。

examination_example.sentence: The result is that the commitments that previously characterized the beginning of adulthood are now being delayed, and new patterns of behavior and a new stage of life are <highlight>emerging</highlight> for those in their twenties.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 结果是，以前标志着成年期开始的责任如今被推迟履行，二十多岁的年轻群体中开始出现新的行为方式和新的生活阶段。

sense_info_list.en: become known; especially as a result of examining something or asking questions about it

examination_example.sentence: Based on what is <highlight>emerging</highlight> from some of this research, that might have been the most rational way to reach a decision.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据这项研究的结果，这可能是做出决定的最合理的方式。

sense_info_list.en: recover from or survive a difficult or demanding situation
